# Security Council Elections Cohort B Members



 ## Description 
Following the guidelines of the [Security Council Charter](https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/OPerating-manual/blob/main/Security%20Council%20Charter%20v0.1.md), the Token House will hold elections for Cohort B of the Optimism Security Council. The top 6 candidates with the highest votes will be elected to Cohort B and serve a 12-month term, subject to Foundation confirmation. If any candidate is not confirmed by the Foundation, the runner up will take their position.


This vote will utilize approval voting, allowing delegates to vote for any number of nominees. In approval or ranked choice votes, delegates may vote for themselves as long as they also cast votes for the remaining elected positions.

* [World Foundation](https://gov.optimism.io/t/security-council-member-self-nomination-world-foundation/9409)
* [Andrey Petrov](https://gov.optimism.io/t/security-council-member-self-nomination-andrey-petrov/9411)
* [OP Labs](https://gov.optimism.io/t/security-council-self-nomination-op-labs/9424)
* [L2BEAT](https://gov.optimism.io/t/security-council-self-nomination-l2beat/9435)
* [Alchemy](https://gov.optimism.io/t/security-council-self-nomination-alchemy/9431)
* [Maggie Love](https://gov.optimism.io/t/security-council-self-nomination-maggie-love-shefi/9439)

* [Martin Tellechea](https://gov.optimism.io/t/security-council-member-self-nomination-martin-tellechea/9471)
* [Ink](https://gov.optimism.io/t/security-council-self-nomination-ink/9473)

* [troy](https://gov.optimism.io/t/security-council-self-nomination-troy/9469)

[This proposal is eligible for Voting Cycle #31b:](https://gov.optimism.io/t/special-voting-cycle-roundup-31b/9457)

It's important to note that no more than 1 elected member may be associated with a particular entity, or that entityâ€™s employees or affiliates.
